ntrol states exercise over their political subdivisions varies greatly, from very tight control in Vermont to relatively little control in Maine. Particular emphasis is placed on the legal relationships between a state and its various types of political subdivisions. The volume concludes with recommendations for the establishment of a state-local governmental partnership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aIntergovernmental cooperation -- United States. 0aIntergovernmental cooperationzUnited States. 0aIntergovernmental fiscal relations -- United States. 0aIntergovernmental fiscal relationszUnited States. 0aState-local relations -- United States. 0aState-local relationszUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438441719?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438441719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438441719/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles